---
description: Run npm/orchestrator/shell commands in the agent environment yourself; do not ask the user to paste commands into their terminal unless execution is impossible (sandbox block, user opt-out).
globs: "**/*"
alwaysApply: true
---

# Execute commands; do not delegate to the user

1. When something needs **`npm`**, **`orchestrator`**, **`bash`**, installs, builds, tests, or **`scripts/install-cursor-global.sh`**, **run it** with the agent’s execution tools.
2. If the sandbox blocks an action (e.g. writing under `~/.cursor`), **request the needed permission** and retry — do not default to “please run this in your terminal” unless the user explicitly prefers that or the environment cannot run commands at all.
3. After running commands, summarize results briefly. Avoid long “copy and paste this block” instructions when you can execute them instead.
